---
import DocsLayout from '../../../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../../../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
import Callout from '../../../../../components/Callout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Your first ticket" description="Deep dive on the full ticket cycle: direct, verify, review, merge.">
  <h1 class="mb-6">Your First Ticket</h1>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-8">After setup, the next ticket is your first real build cycle. You'll direct Claude to implement it, verify the result, read the reviews, and merge. This page walks through every step in detail — after this, you'll know the loop.</p>

  <h2 class="mb-4">Direct Claude</h2>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-2">Open the backlog and find the next ticket. Tell Claude:</p>
  <CodeBlock copy>{`Start Ticket N.`}</CodeBlock>

  <p class="text-text-secondary mt-4 mb-8">That's all you need. Claude reads the backlog, sees what the ticket requires, creates a branch, implements it, commits, pushes, and opens a PR. Watch the VS Code sidebar — files appear in real time.</p>

  <h2 class="mb-4">Verify it works</h2>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-2">Open a second terminal in VS Code (<strong>Ctrl+Shift+`</strong> or the + icon in the terminal panel) and run the dev server. Open the site in your browser.</p>

  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-2">Now check each acceptance criterion from the backlog. This is the core skill — don't just glance at the page and say "looks fine." Check <em>specific things</em>:</p>

  <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
    <div class="border-l-4 border-l-primary bg-primary-bg p-4 rounded-r-lg">
      <p class="font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Visual checks</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Does it look right? Open DevTools (F12) and compare fonts, colours, and spacing against the design spec. Don't eyeball it — measure it.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="border-l-4 border-l-primary bg-primary-bg p-4 rounded-r-lg">
      <p class="font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Functional checks</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Do interactive elements work? Click every link, test every button, try every form input. Check mobile by toggling the device toolbar in DevTools (Ctrl+Shift+M).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="border-l-4 border-l-primary bg-primary-bg p-4 rounded-r-lg">
      <p class="font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Source checks</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Some criteria are invisible — meta tags, semantic HTML, file structure. Use View Page Source, the Elements panel, or the terminal to verify these.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 class="mb-4">Read the Director's Briefing</h2>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">After completing a ticket, Claude provides a Director's Briefing — a summary of what was built, why, and what you should verify. It typically includes:</p>

  <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-5 bg-bg-subtle mb-6">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-3">Example Director's Briefing</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><strong>What was built:</strong> A summary of the implementation — what files were created or changed, and what they do.</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><strong>Key decisions:</strong> Any choices Claude made that weren't spelled out in the ticket — library selection, file structure, approach.</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><strong>What to verify:</strong></p>
    <ul class="text-sm text-text-secondary list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mb-2">
      <li>Specific things to check against the acceptance criteria</li>
      <li>Commands to run to confirm it works</li>
      <li>Pages or features to test in the browser</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary"><strong>Concerns:</strong> Anything Claude is unsure about or wants you to decide on.</p>
  </div>

  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">The Director's Briefing is Claude being transparent about what it did. Your job is to <em>verify</em> those claims, not just trust them. Claude says something is working? Open the browser and check. Claude says a file has the right content? Open it and look.</p>

  <Callout variant="info">
    <p class="text-sm"><strong>This is the skill.</strong> AI will always say "everything works." Your value as a Director is checking whether that's actually true. Sometimes it is. Sometimes it isn't. The habit of verifying is what makes you reliable.</p>
  </Callout>

  <h2 class="mb-4 mt-10">Read the reviews</h2>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Open the PR on GitHub. You'll see two reviews:</p>

  <div class="space-y-4 mb-6">
    <div class="border-l-4 border-l-primary bg-primary-bg p-4 rounded-r-lg">
      <p class="font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Claude's self-review</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Claude compares its own work against the acceptance criteria and reports what passes and what might be an issue. Read this first — it gives you a checklist to verify against.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="border-l-4 border-l-primary bg-primary-bg p-4 rounded-r-lg">
      <p class="font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Gemini's independent review</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Gemini reviews the code for security issues, best practices, and potential bugs. It hasn't seen the code before — it's a fresh pair of eyes. Sometimes it finds real issues. Sometimes it flags things that don't matter for this project. You develop judgment about which is which.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">If you don't understand something in a review, ask Claude:</p>
  <CodeBlock copy>{`Gemini said [paste the comment]. What does that mean? Should I be concerned?`}</CodeBlock>

  <h2 class="mb-4 mt-10">Merge or fix</h2>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">If everything passes your verification and the reviews look clean:</p>
  <CodeBlock copy>{`Everything looks good. Merge it.`}</CodeBlock>

  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">If something is wrong — a criterion fails, or a review flagged a real issue:</p>
  <CodeBlock copy>{`[Describe exactly what's wrong and what it should be instead]. Fix that before we merge.`}</CodeBlock>

  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Be specific. Don't say "it doesn't work" — say exactly what's wrong and what it should be instead. This is the same skill you'd use managing any developer, human or AI.</p>

  <Callout variant="info">
    <p class="text-sm"><strong>That's one complete ticket cycle.</strong> Direct → verify → review → merge (or fix). Every ticket from now on follows this same loop. It gets faster each time because you've done it before.</p>
  </Callout>

  <h2 class="mb-4 mt-10">Common issues on your first ticket</h2>

  <details class="mb-3 border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <summary>"The dev server doesn't start"</summary>
    <div class="p-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Are dependencies installed? Check the Makefile for the right command. Are you in the right directory? Run <code class="bg-bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono">pwd</code> to confirm.</p>
    </div>
  </details>
  <details class="mb-3 border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <summary>"Claude can't push or open a PR"</summary>
    <div class="p-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Run <code class="bg-bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono">gh auth status</code>. If not logged in, run <code class="bg-bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono">gh auth login</code>.</p>
    </div>
  </details>
  <details class="mb-3 border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <summary>"Claude added something not in the backlog"</summary>
    <div class="p-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">This is expected and educational. AI does this constantly. Direct Claude: "The backlog doesn't include [feature]. Remove it." Catching scope creep is one of the most important directing skills.</p>
    </div>
  </details>
  <details class="mb-3 border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <summary>"I'm not sure if the result is correct"</summary>
    <div class="p-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Go back to the backlog. Read the acceptance criteria line by line. For each criterion, check the actual result. If you're still unsure, ask Claude: "The criterion says [X]. Did you do that? Show me where."</p>
    </div>
  </details>
</DocsLayout>
